text: Edward Rogers Bushnell (born December 5, 1876 - January 5, 1951) was an American track and field athlete who competed at the 1900 Summer Olympics in Paris, France. He was born in Republican City, Nebraska. Bushnell competed in the 800 metres. He placed somewhere between fourth and sixth in his first- round (semifinals) heat and did not advance to the final. ==References== * De Wael, Herman. Herman's Full Olympians: "Athletics 1900".
